      "raw_text": "WALLA WALLA, Wash, May S.\nAt a meeting of the Walla Walla\nTrades and Labor Council held last\nFriday night the action of the butch\ners' union regarding the controversy\nthat has been going on for some\ntime with the employers and en-\nployes in the meat markets of Walla\nWall was endorsed. The union butch\ners decided at their meeting held last\nweek that all shops in the city except\none should be declared unfair and all\nunion cards We're removed from these\nshops. There will be no boycott de-\nclared and the union men will con\ntinue to work in the unfair shops\nuntil some future time. The word ha.\nbeen passed around among the mem\nbers of other unions that the shop:\nhave been declared unfair."
    }
